<doc id="102005" wikidata="Q1016934" url="?curid=102005" title="Burrowa-Pine Mountain National Park">
<text>The Burrowa-Pine Mountain National Park is a national park in the Hume region of Victoria, Australia. The national park is situated approximately northeast of Melbourne and east of Albury-Wodonga.

The Pine Mountain, one of the largest monoliths in Australia, is located within the park and is believed to be 1.5 times the size of Uluru. The highest peak in the park is Mount Burrowa at an elevation of above sea level.

